Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.59,0:04:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-早安，探长. -给我两个探长的镜头\N- Good morning,Detective. - I want a shot of the two detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.59,0:04:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}大家退后\NKeep it back,folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.76,0:04:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-你好. -早上好\N- Howdy. - Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.13,0:04:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}在上面\NUp there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.54,0:04:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}进行的如何？\N- How's it going,Gus? - Morning,Pete.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.77,0:04:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-这小子是谁？ -强尼巴兹，是摇滚歌手\N- Who was this fucking guy? - Rock and roll,Gus. Johnny Boz.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.15,0:04:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-从没听说过. -这还用说\N- Never heard of him. - Before your time,cowboy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.58,0:04:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-朗尼，他在哪里？ -楼上右手边房间\N- Hey,Ronny,where they hiding? - Upstairs,to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.85,0:05:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}在六十年代中期有过几首畅销曲子， 在菲尔摩街上有间俱乐部\NMid '60s,had five or six hits. Got a club down on Fillmore now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.65,0:05:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}现在没有了\NNot now,he don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.59,0:05:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}死者在何时死亡的？\N- Do we have a time of death? - Almost.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.83,0:05:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}这是托卡组长\N- Do you guys know Captain Tallcott? - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.30,0:05:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-署长怎么也来了？ -来视察\N- What's the Chief's office doing here? - Observing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.67,0:05:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-法医官，怎样？ -92度，大约6小时前\N- What's it say,Doc? - Ninety-two degrees. About six hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.70,0:05:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}死亡时间约在凌晨两点左右\NPuts time of death at around 2:00 a.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.31,0:05:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}请把那边窗帘拉上\NCan somebody close the drapes over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.74,0:05:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}大约1小时前女佣发现的尸体\NMaid came in about an hour ago and found the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.38,0:05:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-她不是住客. -或许是女佣干的\N- She's not a live-in. - Maybe the maid did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.85,0:05:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}她五十四岁，体重两百四十磅\NShe's 54 years old and weighs 240 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.39,0:05:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-尸体没有淤伤. -不是女佣干的\N- No bruises on the body. - It ain't the maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.09,0:05:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}天知道\NNever know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.19,0:05:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}抱歉\NSorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}别人最后一次见到他 是在午夜他和女友离开俱乐部\NHe was last seen leaving the club with his girlfriend about midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.30,0:05:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-那是什么？ -冰锥，放在咖啡桌上\N- What was it? - Ice pick. Left it in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.44,0:05:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}床单上血迹斑斑\NThere's come stains all over the sheets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.28,0:06:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-真有一套. -他还没玩完就玩完了\N- Very impressive. - He got off before he got off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.89,0:06:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}各位，这件事情十分敏感\NGentlemen,this is sensitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.89,0:06:12.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}巴兹先生对市长竞选贡献良多\NMr. Boz was a major contributor to the mayor's campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.76,0:06:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他同时也是王宫艺术馆委员会的主席\NHe was chairman of the board of the Palace of Fine Arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.26,0:06:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你说他是摇滚乐手\NI thought he was a rock and roll star.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.26,0:06:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他已经退休了\NHe was a retired rock and roll star.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.43,0:06:22.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他是个有头有脸的人\NA civic-minded,very respectable rock and roll star.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.80,0:06:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}那是什么？\NThen,what's that over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.37,0:06:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}看来是有头有脸的可卡因\NLooks like civic-minded, very respectable cocaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.11,0:06:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}听着，这件事搞得我焦头烂额\NListen to me,Curran. I'm gonna get a lot of heat on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.88,0:06:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我不许你出岔错\NI don't want any mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.72,0:06:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他的女友叫什么名字？\NWhat's Boz's girlfriend's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.12,0:06:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}"凯瑟琳楚梅，迪维洛街162号"\N"Catherine Tramell,162 Divisadero."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.40,0:07:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-乐意为您服务，组长. -他本来如日中天\N- Always a pleasure,Captain. - He's up bright and early.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.50,0:07:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}直到被打了十八个洞\NHe doesn't usually punch in 'til after his 18 holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.81,0:07:05.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}强尼和市长一定关系暧昧\NJohnny and the mayor must have been very tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.11,0:07:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}尼克，三点钟别忘了\NNick,keep your 3:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.75,0:07:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你又要我办这案子--\NYou want me to work the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.48,0:07:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我叫你遵命！\N- I said,keep it! - All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.28,0:07:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}好的，我会去\NI'll keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.45,0:07:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你早，我是柯伦探长\NGood morning. I'm Detective Curran. This is Detective Moran.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.72,0:07:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}旧金山警局. 想找凯瑟琳楚梅小姐谈一谈\NSan Francisco Police Department. I'd like to speak to Catherine Tramell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.76,0:07:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}请进\NCome in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.13,0:08:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}请坐，等一下就来\NSit,please. Just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.91,0:08:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}天哪！他俩都有毕加索的画\NAin't that cute? They got his and hers Picasso's.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.21,0:08:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-你连毕加索是谁都搞不清楚. -当然知道，这底下有写\N- I didn't know you knew a Picasso. - Sure I do. It says right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.78,0:08:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}她的比较大\NHers is bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.40,0:08:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}抱歉来打扰你， 只是有几个问题请问一下\NSorry to bother you. We just got a couple of questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.53,0:08:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-是风化组的吗？ -凶杀组的\N- Are you vice? - No,we're homicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.27,0:08:38.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}有何贵干？\NWhat do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.10,0:08:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你上一次见到强尼巴兹是何时？\NWhen was the last time you saw John Boz?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.17,0:08:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他死了？\NIs he dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.78,0:08:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你怎么会认为他死了？\NWhy do you think he's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.78,0:08:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}不然你们来干嘛？\NWell,you wouldn't be here otherwise,would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.38,0:08:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你昨晚和他在一起吗？\NWere you with him last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.45,0:08:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你们找的是凯瑟琳，不是我\NYou're looking for Catherine,not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.22,0:09:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-你又是谁？ -我叫洛茜\N- Who are you? - I'm Roxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.43,0:09:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}是她的朋友\NI'm her friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.43,0:09:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}请问你的朋友在哪里？\NWell,Roxy,do you know where your friend is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.87,0:09:18.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}她在海滩的屋子那里， 海岸路1402号\NShe's out at the beach house at Stenson. Seadrift 1402.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.84,0:09:20.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}谢了\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.18,0:09:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你们在浪费时间\NYou're wasting your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.92,0:09:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}不是凯瑟琳杀的\NCatherine didn't kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.10,0:10:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}楚梅小姐吗？\NMiss Tramell?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.55,0:11:07.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}午安.我是柯伦探长.他是莫伦\NGood afternoon. I'm Detective Curran. This is Detective Moran.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.35,0:11:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-旧金山警局-- -我知道你们是谁\N- We're with the San Francisco Police... - I know who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.26,0:11:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他怎么死的？\NSo,how did he die?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.86,0:11:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}被谋杀\NHe was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.16,0:11:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}显然是的\NObviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.69,0:11:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-怎么被杀的？ -被冰锥杀死的\N- How was he murdered? - With an ice pick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.67,0:11:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你和他在一起约会多久了？\NHow long were you dating him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.91,0:11:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我没和他约会，我和他打炮\NI wasn't dating him. I was fucking him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.44,0:11:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你是职业的吗？\NWhat are you,a pro?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.91,0:11:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我只是业余的\NNo,I'm an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.75,0:11:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你和他的性关系有多久了？\NHow long were you having sex with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}大约一年半\NAbout a year and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.65,0:11:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-你昨晚和他在一起吗？ -是的\N- Were you with him last night? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.16,0:11:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}和他一起离开俱乐部？\NDid you leave the club with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.42,0:11:48.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-是的. -和他一道回家？\N- Yes. - Did you go home with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.89,0:11:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}没有.在俱乐部喝完酒后一起离开\NNo. We had a drink at the club. We left together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.90,0:11:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他回家，我则回到这里\NHe went home, and I came out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.90,0:11:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}昨晚有谁和你在一起吗？\NWas there anyone with you last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.30,0:12:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}没有.昨晚我没心情干那事\NNo. I wasn't in the mood last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.71,0:12:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}有件事问你一下，楚梅小姐\NLet me ask you something, Miss Tramell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.42,0:12:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你为他的死感到难过吗？\NAre you sorry he's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.69,0:12:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}是的\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.72,0:12:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我喜欢操他\NI liked fucking him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.49,0:12:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我不想再多谈了\NLook,I don't really feel like talking anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.13,0:12:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}可不可以到局里谈一下\NListen,lady,we can do this downtown,if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.13,0:12:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}干脆逮捕我好了…\NSo read me my rights and arrest me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.20,0:12:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}那样我就跟你们去\Nand then I'll go downtown.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.34,0:12:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}不然就滚远一点\NOtherwise,get the fuck out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.35,0:12:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}请吧\NPlease.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.58,0:13:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}不简单\NNice girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.63,0:13:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}抱歉！我在外面耽搁了一下\NI'm sorry,Beth. I got hung up in Stenson.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.24,0:13:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-你还好吗，尼克？ -很好啊\N- How are you,Nick? - I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.64,0:13:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}别这样.贝丝，我现在很好. 我们还要耗多久？\NCome on,Beth. You know I'm fine. How long do we have to keep doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.64,0:13:48.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}那得看风纪组的脸色\NAs long as Internal Affairs wants you to,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.71,0:13:50.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-请坐. -胡说八道.你明明知道\N- Have a seat. - It's bullshit. You know it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.75,0:13:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我知道，让我们坐下来， 想法子解决一下，好吗？\NI know it is. But sit down,anyway, so we can get it over with,okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.29,0:14:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}事情如何？\NSo,how are things?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.63,0:14:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}一切顺利\NThings are fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.63,0:14:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我告诉你一切顺利\NI told you,all right? Things are fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.54,0:14:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}私生活如何？\NHow is your personal life?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.50,0:14:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我的性生活十分愉快\NMy sex life is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.54,0:14:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}自从没见到你， 性生活无聊透顶\NMy sex life is actually pretty shitty since I stopped seeing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.25,0:14:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}开始长茧了\NI started developing calluses.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.69,0:14:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}抱歉\NSorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.39,0:14:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}酗酒呢？\NHow's the booze?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.76,0:14:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}三个月来滴酒不沾\NHaven't had a drink in three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.30,0:14:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-药呢？ -没有\N- What about the coke? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.50,0:14:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我工作累的半死. 不碰毒品\NNo. I'm working my ass off. I'm off the sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.70,0:14:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}甚至开始戒烟了\NI even stopped smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.21,0:14:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}戒烟的滋味如何？\NHow is not smoking?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.54,0:14:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}烂透了\NIt sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.48,0:14:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}去告诉风纪组我的身心正常\NNow,will you tell I.A. I'm just your average...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:15:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}是个完全健全的好警察…\Nhealthy, totally fucked up cop...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.35,0:15:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}放我出去吧，求求你？\Nand let me out of here,please?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.66,0:15:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}好的\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.90,0:15:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.24,0:15:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我还在想念你，尼克\NI still miss you,Nick.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.65,0:15:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-尼克，还好吧？ -还好\N- How are you doing? - Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.36,0:15:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}塔克他们在等你\NTallcott's in there. They're waiting. How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.72,0:15:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}她说仍想念我\NShe misses me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.59,0:15:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你这辈子摆脱不了了\NBoy,when that girl mates, it's for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.63,0:15:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}咱们开始吧\NAll right,let's start. Harrigan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.80,0:15:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}颈部和胸部有31处刺伤\NWell,we got 31 stab wounds, neck and the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.33,0:15:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}没有可用的指纹\NNo usable prints, no forceable entry,nothing missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.87,0:15:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}冰锥上也没有指纹. 市场内到处可以买到\NNo prints on the ice pick,either. You can pick it up at any KMart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.67,0:15:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}用的是爱美仕牌的昂贵丝巾\NThe scarf was Hermes. It's expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.71,0:16:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}全世界一年售出两万条\NThey sell about 20,000 a year, worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.85,0:16:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}那个粉末是高纯度的可卡因， 他有吸了一些\NBottle was cocaine. High quality, high content. He inhaled it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.88,0:16:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}嘴唇和生殖器上也沾了一点\NThere were minute quantities on his lips and penis.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.25,0:16:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他留下五百万美元遗产\NMr. Boz leaves $5 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.26,0:16:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}没有直接继承人，也没前科\NNo direct survivors. No criminal record.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.33,0:16:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他喜欢毒品，女孩和摇滚乐\NHe liked his drugs. He liked his girls. He liked his rock and roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.53,0:16:20.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他也喜欢市长，不是吗？\NHe liked the mayor too,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.70,0:16:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他的女友呢？\NWhat about his girlfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.77,0:16:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-她有嫌疑吗？ -她有嫌疑\N- Is she relevant here? Is she a suspect? - She's a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.84,0:16:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}根据什么线索？\NOn what basis?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.48,0:16:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}"女友是三十岁的凯瑟琳楚梅. 没有前科，没有犯罪记录\N"Girlfriend: Catherine Tramell. Age 30. No priors. No convictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.71,0:16:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}一九八三年毕业于柏克莱\NMagna cum laude at Berkeley,1983.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.35,0:16:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}双主修:文学及心理学\NDouble major: Literature and psychology.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.85,0:16:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}父母在七九年一次船难丧生…\NDaughter,sole survivor, Marvin and Elaine Tramell...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.55,0:16:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}她是唯一生还的独生女， 也是唯一财产继承人\Nkilled in a boating accident,1979.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.09,0:16:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}其财富估计为一亿一千万."\NCatherine Tramell,sole heir. Estimated assets: $ 110 million."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.56,0:16:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你没乱盖？\NYou're shitting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.56,0:16:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}"曾嫁给曼尼瓦斯卡…"\N"Formerly engaged to Manuel Vasquez,deceased."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.40,0:16:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你说的是那个曼尼瓦斯卡？\NWhoa,whoa! Manny Vasquez?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.83,0:17:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}没错，前任中量级拳王， 死于八四年一场拳赛\NFormer middleweight contender. Killed in the ring,Atlantic City,1984.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.57,0:17:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}太好了，她有着数亿元身价\NI love it. She's got 100 million bucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.81,0:17:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}他操拳王和摇滚歌手…\NShe fucks fighters and rock and roll stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.91,0:17:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}还有精神病的学位 知道怎样干人的脑袋\Nand she's got a degree in screwing with people's heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.38,0:17:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你忘了她还有文学学位. 她还是个作家\NYou forgot about her degree in literature. She's a writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.41,0:17:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}去年用笔名出版了一本书.猜猜看内容？\NShe published a novel under a pen name. Want to know what it's about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.49,0:17:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}是讲一个被女友谋杀的摇滚歌手\NIt's about a retired rock and roll star who gets murdered by his girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.10,0:17:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}翻到67页，老大\NPage 67,cowboy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.54,0:17:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你猜她怎样对付她的男友？\NYou know how she does the boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.87,0:17:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}在床上用一根冰锥…\NWith an ice pick,in bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.71,0:17:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}用白色丝斤绑在床上\Nhis hands tied with a white silk scarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.72,0:17:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}嘉纳大夫\NDr. Garner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.09,0:17:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我请拉蒙大夫过来讨论. 这件事我担当不起\NI've asked Dr. Lamont to consult with us. This isn't really my turf.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.86,0:18:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}拉蒙大夫在史丹佛大学 教授变态心理…\NDr. Lamont teaches the pathology of psychopathic behavior at Stanford...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.46,0:18:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}也是司法部犯罪心理组的成员\Nand also on the Justice Department Psychological Profile Team.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.13,0:18:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}请说\NDr. Lamont.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.80,0:18:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我想有两种可能\NI see two possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.91,0:18:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}第一点: 写出这本书的人，就是凶手…\NOne: The person who wrote this book is your murderer...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.88,0:18:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}完全根据书上仪式进行杀人\Nand acted out the killing described in ritualistic,literal detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.48,0:18:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}第二点: 有人想嫁祸给本书作者…\NTwo: Someone who wants to harm the writer...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.58,0:18:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}看到这本书正好利用机会\Nread the book and enacted the killing described to incriminate her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.42,0:18:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}若是作者干的，我们该怎么办？\NWhat if the writer did it? Then what are we dealing with?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.89,0:18:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你们面对一个邪恶无比的心灵\NYou're dealing with a devious,diabolical mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.49,0:18:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}这本书在出版之前 至少花了半年才完成--\NYou see,this book had to have been written at least six months...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.13,0:18:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}这表示作者早在构思之前 在潜意识中已经有了计划\Nmaybe even years... before it was published...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.87,0:18:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}这表示作者早在构思之前 在潜意识中已经有了计划\Nwhich means the writer must have planned the crime in the subconscious back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.71,0:18:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}而她执行的方式…\NNow,the fact that she carried it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.11,0:18:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}显示着强烈的变态行为…\Nindicates psychopathic obsessive behavior...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.41,0:18:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}不仅是杀人本身…\Nin terms not only of the killing itself...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.45,0:18:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}而是一种侵略性的强烈本能\Nbut also in terms of the applied advance defense mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.58,0:18:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}有时候我真被搞糊涂了\NSometimes I can't tell shit from shinola,Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.22,0:18:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你刚说的那些字眼是什么意思？\NWhat was all that you just said?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.79,0:19:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-她利用那本书作掩护. -没错\N- She intended the book to be her alibi. - Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.52,0:19:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}一个人会用自己书中描述的方式\NShe's going to say,"Do you think I'd be dumb enough to kill anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.43,0:19:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}去谋杀一个人吗？\Nin the exact way I described in my book?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.63,0:19:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我不会笨到拿自己当嫌疑犯\NI wouldn't do that because I know I'd be the suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.83,0:19:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}假如不是作者呢？ 假设是别人看到这本书？\NSo,what if it's not the writer? What if it's someone who read the book?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.44,0:19:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你面对一位疯狂的杀手…\NYou're dealing,then, with someone so obsessed...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.44,0:19:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}不论是男女 会杀害一切不相关的人…\Nthat he or she is willing to kill an irrelevant and innocent victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.68,0:19:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}只为了嫁祸给本书作者\Nin order to place the blame on the person who wrote that book.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.85,0:19:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}这是一种深藏在内心里的仇恨…\NI'm talking about a deep-seated obsessional hatred...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.72,0:19:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}对于人命毫不尊重\Nand an utter lack of respect for human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.79,0:19:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}所以我们遇到一位千载难逢 世间少见的疯子\NSo,we got a once in a lifetime, top of the line looney-tuney.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.57,0:19:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你是这个意思吗？\NThat's what you're saying, right,Doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.20,0:19:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}这个凶手十分危险…\NYou're dealing with someone very dangerous...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.67,0:19:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}而且变态\Nand very ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.68,0:20:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你明知不可能的. 你根本没有具体证据\NYou know there's no case here. You've got no physical evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.58,0:20:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}她没有不在场证明\NShe hasn't got an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.22,0:20:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}她也没动机. 相信我的话…\NShe hasn't got a motive,either. Believe me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.22,0:20:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}辩护根本会打得我们 无招架之力\Nher defense would just beat us to death with this copycat thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.13,0:20:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}看过这本书的人都有嫌疑\NAnybody who read the book could have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.60,0:20:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-你打算什么都不做？ -我们叫她来问话\N- What do you want to do now? Nothing? - We call her in for questioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.87,0:20:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}她有的是钱， 我们根本弄不过--\NShe's got enough money to burn the department down...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.90,0:20:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}她是最后一位见到死者的人\NShe was the last person seen with the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.51,0:20:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}一切由我负责\NI'll take the responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.18,0:20:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}交给你了\NIt's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.35,0:20:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}这样没用的\NIt won't do any good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.85,0:20:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}她会找个明星律师辩护…\NShe'll just waltz in with some superstar lawyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.22,0:20:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我们只是浪费纳税人的钱\Nwho'll get us all canned for wasting the taxpayers' money.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.12,0:20:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-她一定会那样做. -不会的\N- That's exactly what she'll do. - No,she won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.79,0:20:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我认为她不会找律师\NI don't think she'll hide behind anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.09,0:20:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}她谁都不用找\NI don't think she's gonna hide at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.26,0:20:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}也许她跟你一样神经，柯伦\NThen she's as crazy as you are,Curran.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.14,0:20:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}俗话说得好:\NYou know what they say:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.31,0:20:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}一物克一物\NTakes one to know one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.67,0:21:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我们想请你到局里问话\NMiss Tramell,we'd like you to come downtown to answer a few questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.60,0:21:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你们要逮捕我？\NAre you arresting me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.67,0:21:32.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你喜欢那样吗\NIf that's the way you want to play it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.71,0:21:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我能换一下衣服吗？\NCould I change into something more appropriate?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.15,0:21:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}一下就好，请进\NIt'll only take a minute. Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.35,0:21:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你们随便坐，我马上来\NMake yourselves comfortable. I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.14,0:22:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}加斯\N- Hey,Gus. - Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.61,0:22:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-要花多少时间？ -不知道\N- So,how long is this gonna take? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.42,0:22:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你喜欢保有旧报纸吗？\NDo you always keep old newspapers around?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.09,0:22:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}只收集有趣的新闻\NOnly when they make interesting reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.24,0:22:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-我准备好了. -你可以请律师\N- I'm ready. - You have the right to an attorney.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.41,0:22:39.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我要律师干嘛？\NWhy would I need an attorney?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.22,0:22:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-有烟吗？ -我不吸烟的\N- Do you have a cigarette? - I don't smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.12,0:22:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你会吸烟\NYes,you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.13,0:22:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-我戒了. -恭喜你\N- I quit. - Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.71,0:23:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我以为你自己没烟\NI thought you didn't have any cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.88,0:23:16.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我刚在口袋里找到，要不要？\NOh,I found some in my pocket. Would you like one?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.72,0:23:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}我说过我戒了\NI told you,I quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.85,0:23:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}戒不了多久的\NIt won't last.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.16,0:23:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}-你在写新书吗？ -是的\N- You working on another book? - Yes,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.66,0:23:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}写这种书可真是了不起\NIt must really be something making stuff up all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.30,0:23:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}可以练习说谎\NYeah,it teaches you to lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.44,0:23:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}感觉怎样？\NHow's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.91,0:23:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}你自己编造一些故事，却使人相信. 这称作不定的不信状态\NYou make up believable stuff. It's called suspension of disbelief.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.88,0:23:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}太好了！\NI like that! Suspension of disbelief.
